<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="121" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[136,1452,1310,1841]" pageId="22" pageNumber="121">
Plants cespitose. Culms homomorphic, arching and clambering, 
<quantity box="[936,1031,1346,1373]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="22" pageNumber="121" unit="m" value="4.15" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="0.3">0.3–8 m</quantity>
tall, infra- and supranodal bands of trichomes absent. Profusely branched from the median and upper nodes, without thorns. Leaves not differentiated into culm leaves and foliage leaves. Leaf sheaths without fimbriae at the apex, translucent swelling absent, outer ligule absent, blades large, ovate-lanceolate to lanceolate, midnerve not prominent. Synflorescences terminal, open panicles, the lower branches with male spikelets only, the upper branches with male spikelets below and terminal female spikelets above or female spikelets only; spikelets with filiform pedicels, solitary and unisexual, glumes 2 (female spikelets) or absent (male spikelets), anthecium foveolate (with small pits) only at the apex. Fruit a basic caryopsis, hilum linear, ½–¾ the length of caryopsis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="121" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="22.[136,1452,1310,1841]" pageId="22" pageNumber="121">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soderstrom &amp; Zuloaga" authorityYear="1989" box="[189,325,1634,1660]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Parodiolyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="22" pageNumber="121" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,325,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="121">Parodiolyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an herbaceous bamboo genus mainly characterized by the erect to scandent culms, 
<quantity box="[1307,1400,1634,1661]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.15" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="0.3" pageId="22" pageNumber="121" unit="m" value="4.15" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="0.3">0.3–8 m</quantity>
tall, ovate-lanceolate to lanceolate leaves and synflorescence a terminal panicle, bearing male and female spikelets on the same synflorescence, with female spikelets 
<quantity box="[632,727,1706,1733]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="121" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 mm</quantity>
long, the pedicels filiform and anthecium foveolate (with small pits) only at the apex (Soderstrom &amp; Zuloaga 1981). The genus has four species in 
<collectingCountry box="[1114,1239,1742,1768]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="22" pageNumber="121">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
to South America (
<bibRefCitation author="Kellogg, E. A." box="[144,306,1778,1805]" pageId="22" pageNumber="121" refId="ref25159" refString="Kellogg, E. A. (2015) The Families and Genera of Vascular Plants Volume XIII. Flowering Plants Monocots: Poaceae. Springer International Publishing, Switzerland, 413 pp." type="book" year="2015">Kellogg 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Oliveira, I. L. C. &amp; Oliveira, R. P. &amp; Carvalho, M. L. S." box="[320,567,1778,1804]" pageId="22" pageNumber="121" pagination="2020" refId="ref26013" refString="Oliveira, I. L. C., Oliveira, R. P. &amp; Carvalho, M. L. S. (2020 c) Parodiolyra In: Flora do Brasil 2020, Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 13423 (accessed 9 October 2021)." type="book chapter" year="2020">
Oliveira 
<emphasis box="[423,483,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="121">et al.</emphasis>
2020c
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[624,695,1778,1804]" name="Brazil" pageId="22" pageNumber="121">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, three species occur in the Amazon and Mata Atlântica domains (
<bibRefCitation author="Oliveira, I. L. C. &amp; Oliveira, R. P. &amp; Carvalho, M. L. S." box="[144,380,1814,1840]" pageId="22" pageNumber="121" pagination="2020" refId="ref26013" refString="Oliveira, I. L. C., Oliveira, R. P. &amp; Carvalho, M. L. S. (2020 c) Parodiolyra In: Flora do Brasil 2020, Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 13423 (accessed 9 October 2021)." type="book chapter" year="2020">
Oliveira 
<emphasis box="[244,300,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="121">et al.</emphasis>
2020c
</bibRefCitation>
). In the Serra do Cachimbo, it is represented by one species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
